row.cell:
(a) It is a guerrilla war, of small-scale operations, in jungle
                                and difficult terrain, where advanced weapons, air power, and
                                large-unit formations are not of decisive importance;

(b) it is a “war of national liberation”—a political and social
                                struggle—the kind of struggle which they believe they will
                                inevitably win;

(b) extended to airfields and SAM
                                sites near Hanoi (and done with SAC
                                aircraft);
